SQL-02
Department Salary Rankings
Medium
Problem
Rank employees by salary within their department. Show both RANK (with gaps) and DENSE_RANK (no gaps). Also show the top earner per department.
Solution
-- Part 1: Rank all employees within department
SELECT
    name,
    department,
    salary,
    RANK() OVER (
        PARTITION BY department
        ORDER BY salary DESC
    ) AS salary_rank,
    DENSE_RANK() OVER (
        PARTITION BY department
        ORDER BY salary DESC
    ) AS dense_rank
FROM employees
ORDER BY department, salary_rank;

-- Part 2: Get ONLY the top earner per department
WITH ranked AS (
    SELECT name, department, salary,
        DENSE_RANK() OVER (
            PARTITION BY department ORDER BY salary DESC
        ) AS rnk
    FROM employees
)
SELECT name, department, salary
FROM ranked
WHERE rnk = 1;
RANK vs DENSE_RANK: If two people tie at rank 1, RANK gives both rank 1 but skips rank 2 (next is 3). DENSE_RANK gives both rank 1 and the next person gets rank 2 — no gaps. Use DENSE_RANK when filtering top-N to avoid missing ties.